data.title: Britney Spears Introduces Sister Jamie Lynn Onstage at Grand Ole Opry
data.meta_description: Britney Spears has been busy with her revamped Las Vegas show Piece of Me, but she still made time to show some sisterly love.
data.text:
Britney Spears has been busy with her revamped Las Vegas show Piece of Me, but she still made time to show some sisterly love. Last night (March 15), Britney made a surprise appearance and introduced Jamie Lynn Spears onstage for her performance at the historic Grand Ole Opry in Nashville.

Britney Spears Wishes You a ‘Happy Friday!’ With Saucy Bikini Video

Former teen actress Jamie Lynn has been creating a music career of her own as a country artist and songwriter for the past few years. She hit the Billboard Hot 100 chart (Oct. 31) in 2015, as a co-writer on Jana Kramer‘s single “I Got The Boy,” and her EP, without a label, debuted at No. 193 on the Billboard 200 albums.

Trending on Billboard

Jamie Lynn Spears‘ Country Career Gathers Pace

Britney was joined by their brother Bryan as they proudly welcomed Jamie Lynn, who shared videos of the night and thank you’s on social media for the family support. Check out posts from the night below.
